claim.claim-text:
1. A power supply arrangement for passing power through a connector having a limited ampacity, comprising: 
a load having a predetermined voltage and amperage requirement; 
a power source having a voltage higher than said load requirement and producing a current lower than said load requirement; 
a converter means for converting said source of high voltage at low current to a lower voltage at higher current; 
the output of said power source being coupled through said connector to the input of said converter means; and 
the output of said converter means being coupled to said load.

3. A power supply arrangement for passing power through a connector having a limited ampacity comprising: 
an intermittent load having a predetermined voltage and amperage requirement; 
a power source having a voltage approximately equal to said predetermined voltage requirement, and producing a current less than said amperage requirement; 
a capacitance; 
said power source being coupled through said connector to said capacitance; and 
said intermittent load being coupled to said capacitance.
